sql:
SELECT category_name
FROM rating_categories
WHERE is_mandatory = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'sprouted after the New Year's bell tolled in 2023' refers to teams that started after '2022-12-31';
- 'blossoming members' refers to students;
- 'average final score' is the mean of all final scores for the students in each team.

- "shining stars" refers to the top-performing students in each team;
- "ensemble" refers to the team;
- "collective applause" refers to the overall average rating;
- "diversity of their performances" refers to the number of rating categories.

- "steered their teams through the initial project phase" refers to students with the role of 'Leader' in the team;
- "the stormy years of 2020 to 2022" refers to the evaluation dates between '2020-01-01' and '2022-12-31';
- "initial project phase" refers to teams working on project ID 1.

- 'Above Average' means a student's average score is higher than the team's average score;
- 'More than 2 students' means the team has at least 3 students;
- 'Team ID' is a unique identifier for each team.

- "stars that shine the brightest" refers to teams with the highest average rating in their respective categories;
- "team performance" is evaluated through ratings in different categories;
- "average rating" is the mean score received by the team in the evaluations.

- "Top-performing students" are those with the highest average ratings based on the latest evaluation;
- "Average team rating" is the mean of the average ratings of all students in the team;
- "Teams with the most top-performing students" are those with the highest count of students who have the highest average ratings.

- 'shining stars' refers to students who have a role of 'Leader' in their team;
- 'showered them with praise' refers to an average rating greater than 0.8;
- 'most esteemed' refers to the order of results based on the highest average ratings.

- "shining stars" refers to teams with exceptional performance;
- "brightest student" refers to the student with the highest final score in the team;
- "outshines the average brilliance" means the student's score is higher than the average score of all students.

- "average rating" refers to the mean score given to students by evaluators;
- "total score" is the sum of all final scores of the students in a team;
- "latest evaluation" refers to the most recent evaluation date for each student.

- 'Blossoms blooming after the year 2020' refers to students who enrolled after 2020;
- 'Shone brightly' refers to achieving an average rating greater than 0.5;
- 'Halfway mark' refers to the value 0.5;
- 'CC' category is a specific type of rating category in the context of the project evaluations.
